{@--1@} To stoop, bend
down (as an elephant to strike
with his tusks);  
{#vaprakrIqApariRatagajaprekzaRIyaM dadarSa#} <ls>Me. 2</ls>; {#vizke nAgaH#} 
{#paryaRaMsIt sva eva#} <ls>Śi. 18. 27.</ls>

{@--2@} To bend or
bow down, be inclined;  
{#lajjApariRatEH (vadanakamalEH)#} <ls>Bh. 1. 4.</ls>

{@--3@} To be
changed or transformed into, 
assume the form of (with <ab>instr.</ab>);
{#latABAvena pariRatamasyA rUpaM#} <ls>V. 4</ls>;  
<ls n="V.">4. 28</ls>; {#kzIraM jalaM vA svayameva daDihimaBAvena#} 
{#pariRamate#} <ls>Ś. B.</ls>; <ls>Me. 45.</ls>

{@--5@} To be developed or matured,
be ripe; <ls>Me. 18</ls>; <ls>Ki. 5. 37</ls>;
<ls>M. 3. 8</ls>; <ls>Rs. 1. 26</ls>; <ls>Mv. 1. 12</ls>;
see {#pariRata#} below.

{@--7@} To set, decline in
the west (as the sun); {#anena samayena#}
{#pariRato divasaH#} <ls>K. 47.</ls>

{@--1@}
To make ripe, mature, develop, 
perfect.
